====Adjective====
{{en-adj|er}}

# Having much [[distance]] from one terminating point on an object or an area to another terminating point {{qualifier|usually applies to [[horizontal]] dimensions; see Usage Notes below}}.
#: ''It's a '''long''' way from the Earth to the Moon.''
# Having great [[duration]].
#: ''The pyramids of Egypt have been around for a '''long''' time.''
# {{British|dialect}} Not [[short]]; [[tall]].
# {{finance}} possessing or owning [[stocks]], [[bonds]], commodities or other financial instruments with the aim of benefiting of the expected rise in their value.
#: ''I'm '''long''' in DuPont.''
#: ''I have a '''long''' position in DuPont.'''
# {{cricket}} of a [[fielding]] [[position]], close to the [[boundary]] (or closer to the boundary than the equivalent [[short]] position)
# {{tennis}} (speaking of the ball) that bounces behind the [[baseline]] (and therefore is ''out''). 
#* ''No! That forehand is '''long'''...''

